ale tests using deprecated org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor/TypedProps APIs that are present in 1.1.5 but absent from 2.0.0-M1; this needs test/API adaptation rather than setup.\",\n    \"Pekko docs mention pekko-testkit as a test-scope helper for classic actor testing, but meaningful coverage can still be written directly against pekko-actor with ActorSystem, Props, ask/latches, and config, so it is not a required deterministic setup dependency.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0310ab4ce8da916a016a4074b4461c8193bc550368c3594cc4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 801, "output": 949, "cacheRead": 24576, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 26326, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782609065198, "responseId": "resp_0310ab4ce8da916a016a4074a9c1fc8193a5559e20e6781a93"}}
